CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 13, 1941, pg. 2, reads: "Entire Community Pays Last Respects To Al Jackson - Impressive ceremonies marked the final rites for Alter Jackson, young businessman, who was drowned during Labor Day weekend. Picture here shows procession taking body from home to hearse.- Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Six men walking casket into hearse with Clyde C. Davis funeral home sign in window, and men and women gathered around for Alter Jackson funeral
